      "summary": "The broadcast runtime option API is a dead abstraction: option hooks are accepted but never applied, creating misleading extension points and silent configuration bypass.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go",
        "goseg/startup_orchestrator.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`Initialize` is declared as `func Initialize(options ...broadcastRuntimeOption) error` but only contains `_ = options`, never executing or storing any injected option.",
        "There is no follow-up call path that applies or validates options before `bootstrapBroadcastState`, so callers cannot influence bootstrap behavior through this seam.",
        "Startup always invokes `broadcast.Initialize()` directly with no options, matching the non-usage pattern."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Either remove the unused `broadcastRuntimeOption` extension hook or implement it by applying each option to configure init behavior in a single, explicit place inside `Initialize` (for example, injecting alternate runtimes, config sources, or initialization policies). Then add unit tests that assert non-default options alter initialization.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_option_leakage"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "runtime_seam_overlayer_cluster",
      "summary": "Service-specific runtime adapter layers are overly verbose and mostly pass-through, adding indirection without introducing meaningful service-specific policy.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_seams.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/wireguard.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/netdata.go",
        "goseg/config/wireguard.go"
